messageBody:
Paige,
Thank you for spotting those errors. I study several Memrise courses on a daily basis, and most of them at least a few errors. I find that the occasional errors don't really get in the way of my learning that much, and I usually discover them on my own at a certain point, although sometimes months or years later. Since my initial goal is just to be able to read, not write, Quickscript, I'm finding that Memrise is helping a lot.

I think the Memrise course was created by a member of this group, called trybloganatgmail. Perhaps he'll see this thread and make some corrections.
